10.44	The_Moving_Finger	The Moving Finger	The Moving Finger is detective fiction novel by Agatha Christie, first published in the US by Dodd, Mead and Company in July 1942 and in UK by the Collins Crime Club in June 1943 The U.S. edition retailed at $2.00 and the UK edition at seven shillings and sixpence (7/6). It features the elderly detective Miss Marple in a relatively minor, deus ex machina-like role, appearing more than halfway through and in only a handful of scenes.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/4/48/The_Moving_Finger_First_Edition_Cover_1942.jpg
